1
00:00:00,080 --> 00:00:04,436
In a methods course or research team, the valuable conversation

2
00:00:04,436 --> 00:00:08,793
is why a passage was coded in a particular way.

3
00:00:08,793 --> 00:00:13,149
QualCanvas keeps the excerpt, definition and developing structure visible enough

4
00:00:13,149 --> 00:00:14,456
to discuss together.

5
00:00:14,856 --> 00:00:21,646
The institutions page outlines options for methods teaching, labs and governed deployments.

6
00:00:21,646 --> 00:00:27,305
Confirm procurement, hosting and data-processing requirements before a cohort uploads

7
00:00:27,305 --> 00:00:29,568
any real participant material.

8
00:00:29,968 --> 00:00:34,752
Begin a calibration exercise with explicit definitions and passage boundaries.

9
00:00:34,752 --> 00:00:39,536
Ask learners to code independently before showing the class distribution,

10
00:00:39,536 --> 00:00:44,320
so the result reflects their decisions rather than group influence.

11
00:00:44,720 --> 00:00:48,920
Agreement metrics can identify codes or excerpts that need discussion.

12
00:00:48,920 --> 00:00:53,120
Open the disagreements, ask each coder to explain the reasoning

13
00:00:53,120 --> 00:00:57,320
and revise the codebook only when the discussion supports a

14
00:00:57,320 --> 00:00:58,160
clearer rule.

15
00:00:58,560 --> 00:01:04,093
For teaching, prefer synthetic transcripts or material licensed for classroom use.

16
00:01:04,093 --> 00:01:09,123
Share only with the intended cohort, and remove access when

17
00:01:09,123 --> 00:01:10,632
the exercise ends.

18
00:01:11,032 --> 00:01:16,353
The same structure supports a research team: define roles, schedule

19
00:01:16,353 --> 00:01:20,078
independent coding, review disagreements and document decisions.

20
00:01:20,078 --> 00:01:26,464
Real-time tools make coordination easier, but the team still owns the method.

21
00:01:26,864 --> 00:01:31,517
Whether you are teaching a class or coordinating a lab,

22
00:01:31,517 --> 00:01:36,170
keep the evidence shared, the initial judgement independent and the

23
00:01:36,170 --> 00:01:37,100
review documented.

24
00:01:37,100 --> 00:01:41,288
That builds confidence without pretending qualitative interpretation is mechanical.
